---
const title = 'Process — AxiClaw';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <style>
      body{margin:0;font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial; background:#fff; color:#111;}
      a{color:inherit;text-decoration:none;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.15)}
      header,main{padding:42px 20px;}
      .wrap{max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;}
      h1{margin:0 0 12px;letter-spacing:-.02em}
      p,li{color:#333;line-height:1.6}
      .muted{color:#666}
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <div class="wrap">
        <a href="/">← Home</a>
        <h1>Process</h1>
        <p class="muted">SVG → AxiDraw. Dense, but not destructive.</p>
      </div>
    </header>
    <main>
      <div class="wrap">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Generate</strong> vector systems (streamlines, bands, ridges) with parameter logs.</li>
          <li><strong>Constrain</strong> curvature and local density to avoid “killer zones”.</li>
          <li><strong>Filter</strong> SVG with anti-overdraw / anti-dwell (cap repeated hits per area).</li>
          <li><strong>Preview</strong> raster from the filtered SVG.</li>
          <li><strong>Plot</strong> on demand, with camera snapshots and timelapse.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
